  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis ã jobsquare\n\n**Baseline: zero test coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no test files anywhere in the repo, `pytest` isn't even installed in `.venv`, and `.github/workflows/scrape.yaml` runs the scraper but never runs tests. Every one of the ~90 functions across 8 modules (1,932 LOC) is untested. Below is the gap analysis by module, ordered by risk, with skeletons for representative gaps in each category (the ATS parsers repeat a small set of edge-case shapes, so I give full skeletons for a few and enumerate the rest in a table rather than repeating near-identical code 20 times).\n\n**Suggested test setup** (none of this exists yet):\n```\npip install pytest pytest-asyncio respx freezegun\n```\n`respx` mocks `httpx` at the transport layer (needed for every `fetch_*` function); `freezegun` needed for anything touching `datetime.now()` (models.py, store.py, agent.py's db-new/db-mark).\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` ã highest value, zero risk to test, currently 0% covered\n\n**Untested:** `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`.\n\n**Edge cases not covered:**\n- `parse_posted_at`: empty string, `None`-ish falsy input, negative epoch, epoch boundary exactly at `1_000_000_000_000` (ms vs s ambiguity), Workday prose (\"Posted 3 Days Ago\" ã currently falls through to `fromisoformat` and returns `None`, silently), trailing `Z`, already-aware ISO string, malformed garbage string.\n- `Job.content_hash`: two jobs differing only in `posted_at`/`salary_range` must hash identically (by design ã `content_hash` deliberately excludes those fields); this invariant is never asserted anywhere.\n- `Job.key` collision: same `external_id` across different `source`/`company` must NOT collide.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None  # type: ignore[arg-type]\n\n    def test_lever_millisecond_epoch(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_second_epoch_boundary_not_misread_as_ms(self):\n        # just under 1e12 -> must be treated as seconds, not ms\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"999999999\")\n        assert dt.year == 2001\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_trailing_z(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T00:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T00:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        # Workday's \"Posted 3 Days Ago\" ã must not raise\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none_not_raise(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not-a-date\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **overrides):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\")\n        return Job(**{**base, **overrides})\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_and_distinguishes_source(self):\n        a = self._job(source=\"greenhouse\")\n        b = self._job(source=\"lever\")\n        assert a.key != b.key\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_posted_at_and_salary(self):\n        a = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\", salary_range=\"100k\")\n        b = self._job(posted_at=\"2025-06-01\", salary_range=\"200k\")\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title_change(self):\n        a = self._job(title=\"Engineer\")\n        b = self._job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")\n        assert a.content_hash != b.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_and_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert \"key\" in row and \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` ã pure logic, easy to test, currently 0% covered\n\n**Untested:** `match`, `filter_jobs`, `_compile`.\n\n**Edge cases not covered:**\n- Word-boundary regex behavior: `include=[\"go\"]` must not match \"Django\" or \"Google\" (the `\\b` boundary is the whole point of `_compile` and is unverified).\n- Empty/`None` `include`/`exclude`/`locations` lists (all falsy-guarded ã never exercised).\n- `cutoff` set but `job.posted_dt` is `None` (unparseable) ã code comment says \"keep postings whose timestamp we couldn't parse rather than nuke them\" ã this exact behavior is unverified.\n- Exclude takes priority over include when both match.\n- Case-insensitivity of keyword and location matching.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(title=\"\", department=\"\", location=\"\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n               url=\"u\", department=department, location=location, posted_at=posted_at)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_include_word_boundary_does_not_match_substring(self):\n        # \"go\" must not match inside \"Django\"/\"Google\"\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Django Developer\"), include=[\"go\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_matches_whole_word_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Senior Go Engineer\"), include=[\"go\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_wins_even_if_include_also_matches(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Senior Python Intern\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"python\"], exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\n    def test_no_filters_passes_everything(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Anything\")) is True\n\n    def test_locations_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(location=\"Remote - New York, NY\"),\n                     locations=[\"new york\"]) is True\n\n    def test_locations_no_match_excludes(self):\n        assert match(_job(location=\"London\"), locations=[\"new york\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_confirmed_old_posting(self):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat()\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=old), cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=\"not a date\"), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_fresh_posting(self):\n        recent = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=recent), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_builds_cutoff(self):\n        old = _job(title=\"A\", posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n                    - timedelta(days=100)).isoformat())\n        new = _job(title=\"B\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        result = filter_jobs([old, new], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n        assert result == [new]\n\n    def test_empty_rules_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [_job(title=\"A\"), _job(title=\"B\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` ã the dedup source of truth, zero coverage, highest correctness risk\n\n**Untested:** entire `Store` class ã schema creation, migration, `diff` (the core dedup logic), `get_meta`/`set_meta`, `next_seq`, `added_since`, `count`.\n\n**Missing scenarios that matter most:**\n- `diff()`: brand-new job ã goes to `new`; unchanged job (same content_hash) ã goes to neither, but `last_seen` still updates; changed job (different content_hash) ã goes to `changed`, row updated in place.\n- `_migrate()`: opening a pre-existing DB file that lacks the `salary_range` column (simulates upgrading an old `jobs.db`) ã this is exactly the scenario the migration exists for and it's unverified.\n- `next_seq`: sequential calls increment monotonically; concurrent/interleaved calls don't collide (the `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` locking claim is untested).\n- `added_since`: ordering (oldest first) and strict `>` boundary (a row with `first_seen == ts` must be excluded).\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) actually closes the connection.\n\n**Missing error-handling tests:** none of the SQL calls are guarded ã worth a test that a duplicate `key` via manual insert / constraint doesn't crash `diff` (currently `PRIMARY KEY` conflict would only occur via a bug, so this is a regression guard).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport pytest\nimport sqlite3\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef _job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", company=\"acme\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=company, external_id=external_id,\n               title=title, url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\")\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_first_seen_job_is_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither_new_nor_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_content_change_reports_as_changed_not_new(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n        assert new == []\n        assert len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_diff_persists_across_store_instances(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        with Store(path) as s1:\n            s1.diff([_job()])\n        with Store(path) as s2:\n            new, _ = s2.diff([_job()])\n            assert new == []  # still known\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_opens_pre_salary_range_schema_without_error(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"old.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        s = Store(path)  # must not raise\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n        s.close()\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n    def test_set_then_get_meta_roundtrips(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v1\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_overwrites(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_starts_at_one_and_increments(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"seq\") == 1\n        assert store.next_seq(\"seq\") == 2\n\n    def test_independent_keys_dont_interfere(self, store):\n        store.next_seq(\"a\")\n        assert store.next_seq(\"b\") == 1\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_excludes_rows_at_exact_boundary(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert store.added_since(row[\"first_seen\"]) == []\n\n    def test_orders_oldest_first(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(external_id=\"1\")])\n        store.conn.execute(\"UPDATE jobs SET first_seen = '2020-01-01T00:00:00+00:00'\")\n        store.diff([_job(external_id=\"2\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"2019-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert [r[\"external_id\"] for r in rows] == [\"1\", \"2\"]\n\nclass TestCount:\n    def test_empty_store_is_zero(self, store):\n        assert store.count() == 0\n\n    def test_reflects_inserted_rows(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(\"1\"), _job(\"2\")])\n        assert store.count() == 2\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `notify.py` ã external-facing side effects, zero coverage, real risk of silent notification failure\n\n**Untested:** every `notify_*` function, `_sms_body`, `dispatch`.\n\n**Missing scenarios:**\n- Each `notify_*` early-returns when its env var(s) are unset ã none of these guards are tested.\n- Each early-returns when `new` and `changed` are both empty even if the env var IS set ã untested.\n- `dispatch`'s exception isolation: one notifier raising must not prevent the others from running (this is the actual resilience guarantee of the module and it's unverified).\n- `_sms_body`: truncation at `limit`, the \"+N more\" line, ASCII-only compactness.\n- `notify_sms` calls `resp.raise_for_status()` ã a 4xx from Twilio should propagate as an exception (which `dispatch` then swallows and logs) ã untested boundary.\n- `notify_webhook`/`notify_slack` actually construct the right JSON ã no assertion anywhere on payload shape.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom httpx import Response\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef _job(title=\"Eng\", company=\"acme\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=company, external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"https://x\")\n\nclass TestNotifySlack:\n    def test_noop_without_env_var(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        # no respx mock registered -> any HTTP call would raise; absence of\n        # a call is the assertion\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n\n    def test_noop_when_no_new_or_changed(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n        notify.notify_slack([], [])  # must not POST\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_posts_new_job_summary(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n        route = respx.post(\"https://hooks.slack.com/x\").mock(\n            return_value=Response(200))\n        notify.notify_slack([_job(title=\"Backend Eng\")], [])\n        assert route.called\n        assert \"Backend Eng\" in route.calls[0].request.content.decode()\n\nclass TestNotifySms:\n    def test_noop_unless_all_four_env_vars_set(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])  # missing token -> no call\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_4xx(self, monkeypatch):\n        for k, v in {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n                     \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}.items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        respx.post(url__regex=r\".*Messages\\.json\").mock(\n            return_value=Response(400, json={\"message\": \"bad number\"}))\n        with pytest.raises(Exception):\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_and_shows_remainder_count(self):\n        jobs = [_job(title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n        assert body.count(\"- Role\") == 8\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_failing_does_not_block_others(self, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        calls = []\n        monkeypatch.setattr(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [\n            lambda n, c: (_ for _ in ()).throw(RuntimeError(\"boom\")),\n            lambda n, c: calls.append(\"second\"),\n        ])\n        notify.dispatch([_job()], [])\n        assert calls == [\"second\"]\n        assert \"boom\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `pipeline.py` ã the orchestration entrypoint, zero coverage, only integration-tested implicitly by running the whole CLI\n\n**Untested:** `load_config` (defaults), `run` (dry-run vs persisting path), `run_sync`.\n\n**Missing scenarios:**\n- `load_config`: defaults for missing `sources`/`filters`/`db`/`concurrency` keys applied correctly; a config that already sets these isn't overwritten.\n- `run(dry_run=True)`: must NOT touch `Store` at all (no `jobs.db` side effects) and returns `{\"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}` unconditionally regardless of matches.\n- `run(dry_run=False)`: exercises the full fetch ã filter ã diff ã dispatch ã count chain ã this is the one true integration test gap; currently nothing verifies these four modules compose correctly.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport yaml\nfrom models import Job\nimport pipeline\n\nclass TestLoadConfig:\n    def test_fills_in_defaults(self, tmp_path):\n        p = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        p.write_text(yaml.dump({}))\n        cfg = pipeline.load_config(p)\n        assert cfg == {\"sources\": [], \"filters\": {}, \"db\": \"jobs.db\", \"concurrency\": 8}\n\n    def test_preserves_explicit_values(self, tmp_path):\n        p = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        p.write_text(yaml.dump({\"concurrency\": 2, \"db\": \"custom.db\"}))\n        cfg = pipeline.load_config(p)\n        assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 2 and cfg[\"db\"] == \"custom.db\"\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRun:\n    async def test_dry_run_never_touches_store(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": [], \"db\": str(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\")}))\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[\n            Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n        ])):\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n        assert not (tmp_path / \"jobs.db\").exists()\n\n    async def test_full_run_persists_and_dispatches(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": [], \"db\": str(db_path)}))\n        job = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[job])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 1, \"changed\": 0}\n        mock_dispatch.assert_called_once()\n        assert db_path.exists()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `fetchers.py` ã largest file (1,146 LOC), highest business risk, zero coverage\n\nThis file has two layers: pure `parse_*` functions (the module docstring explicitly says these are \"unit-testable against mocked transports without touching the network\" ã a stated intent that's never been acted on) and `fetch_*` async I/O functions that need `respx`.\n\n#### 6a. Infrastructure primitives ã untested and load-bearing for every fetcher\n\n- `_request`: retry-on-`429/500/502/503/504`, exponential backoff+jitter, exhausting retries raises `RuntimeError` wrapping the last error, non-retryable 4xx (e.g. 401/403) fails immediately without retrying.\n- `_balanced_json`: nested braces, braces inside string literals (must not be miscounted), escaped quotes inside strings, unterminated input returns `None`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_core.py\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nimport httpx\nfrom fetchers import _request, _balanced_json\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRequest:\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self):\n        route = respx.get(\"https://x.test/j\").mock(side_effect=[\n            httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True}),\n        ])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x.test/j\", retries=3)\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n        assert route.call_count == 2\n\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises(self):\n        respx.get(\"https://x.test/j\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x.test/j\", retries=2)\n\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_non_retryable_4xx_fails_without_exhausting_retries(self):\n        route = respx.get(\"https://x.test/j\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(401))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x.test/j\", retries=4)\n        assert route.call_count == 1  # no retry on 401\n\n\nclass TestBalancedJson:\n    def test_simple_object(self):\n        assert _balanced_json('{\"a\":1}', 0) == '{\"a\":1}'\n\n    def test_nested_braces(self):\n        text = '{\"a\":{\"b\":1}}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_brace_inside_string_not_counted(self):\n        text = '{\"a\":\"} not a close\"}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_escaped_quote_inside_string(self):\n        text = r'{\"a\":\"esc\\\"aped\"}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_unterminated_returns_none(self):\n        assert _balanced_json('{\"a\":1', 0) is None\n```\n\n#### 6b. `parse_*` functions ã the single highest-value, lowest-cost gap in the codebase\n\nEvery parser has the same untested edge-case shape: missing optional keys, empty result arrays, `isListed: False` / dedup filtering (Ashby), malformed nested location dicts, and required-key `KeyError` behavior when a source omits `id`/`title` (several parsers do `j[\"id\"]` unguarded ã e.g. `parse_greenhouse`, `parse_lever`, `parse_smartrecruiters` ã a source returning a job without an `id` currently crashes the whole fetch instead of skipping that one row, and nothing documents or tests this).\n\nFull skeleton for `parse_greenhouse` (representative) plus the trickier bespoke ones (`_amazon_posted_at`, `_apple_hydration`, `_ds1_posted_at`, `_bd_location`) that have real parsing-logic bugs waiting to happen:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary,\n                       parse_ashby, _amazon_posted_at, _apple_hydration,\n                       _apple_posted_at, _ds1_posted_at, _bd_location,\n                       parse_google, parse_apple)\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_maps_fields(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\", \"absolute_url\": \"https://x\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}, {\"name\": \"Infra\"}],\n                           \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert jobs[0].department == \"Eng, Infra\"\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"NYC\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_location_defaults_empty(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\"}]}\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)[0].location == \"\"\n\n    def test_job_missing_id_raises(self):\n        # documents current (crash) behavior ã a source dropping `id` kills fetch_source\n        import pytest\n        with pytest.raises(KeyError):\n            parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"title\": \"Eng\"}]})\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_min_and_max_formatted_with_commas(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000ã150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description_when_no_range(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_skips_unlisted_jobs(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"Hidden\"},\n                          {\"id\": \"2\", \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n        assert [j.external_id for j in jobs] == [\"2\"]\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_date_normalizes_to_iso(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_string_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Marchember 1, 2026\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_empty_input_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestApplePostedAt:\n    def test_trims_nanosecond_precision_to_microseconds(self):\n        result = _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:30:00.812668311Z\")\n        assert result == \"2024-01-15T10:30:00.812668+00:00\"\n\n    def test_no_fractional_seconds(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\") == \"2024-01-15T10:30:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_empty_or_none_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n        assert _apple_posted_at(None) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestAppleHydration:\n    def test_extracts_and_double_decodes_json(self):\n        html = ('window.__staticRouterHydrationData = JSON.parse(\"'\n                r'{\\\"loaderData\\\":{\\\"a\\\":1}}' + '\");')\n        assert _apple_hydration(html) == {\"loaderData\": {\"a\": 1}}\n\n    def test_missing_marker_returns_none(self):\n        assert _apple_hydration(\"<html></html>\") is None\n\n    def test_malformed_json_returns_none_not_raise(self):\n        html = 'window.__staticRouterHydrationData = JSON.parse(\"{not json\");'\n        assert _apple_hydration(html) is None\n\n    def test_escaped_quote_inside_blob_does_not_truncate_early(self):\n        html = (r'window.__staticRouterHydrationData = JSON.parse(\"{\\\"a\\\":\\\"esc\\\\\\\"aped\\\"}\"'\n                 ');')\n        assert _apple_hydration(html) == {\"a\": 'esc\"aped'}\n\n\nclass TestDs1PostedAt:\n    def test_prefers_create_time_index_12_over_later_indices(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[12] = [1700000000]\n        job[13] = [1800000000]\n        result = _ds1_posted_at(job)\n        assert \"2023\" in result  # index 12's timestamp wins\n\n    def test_short_array_no_timestamp_indices_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([1, \"title\"]) == \"\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_index_13_when_12_empty(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[13] = [1700000000]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n\n\nclass TestBdLocation:\n    def test_walks_parent_chain_city_to_country(self):\n        city = {\"en_name\": \"Seattle\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"Washington\",\n                 \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\", \"parent\": None}}}\n        assert _bd_location(city) == \"Seattle, Washington, USA\"\n\n    def test_none_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_name_when_no_en_name(self):\n        assert _bd_location({\"name\": \"Tokyo\", \"parent\": None}) == \"Tokyo\"\n\n\nclass TestParseGoogle:\n    def test_skips_falsy_first_element(self):\n        # j[0] falsy is an explicit skip-guard in the source\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [[None, \"title\"], [0, \"title\"]]) == []\n\n    def test_short_array_defensive_indexing(self):\n        # only index 0 present; title/locations/posted_at must all default safely\n        jobs = parse_google(\"google\", [[\"id123\"]])\n        assert jobs[0].title == \"\"\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseApple:\n    def test_dedupes_repeated_location_strings(self):\n        results = [{\"id\": \"1-0001\", \"positionId\": \"1\", \"postingTitle\": \"Eng\",\n                    \"locations\": [{\"city\": \"Cupertino\", \"countryName\": \"USA\"},\n                                  {\"city\": \"Cupertino\", \"countryName\": \"USA\"}]}]\n        jobs = parse_apple(\"apple\", results)\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"Cupertino, USA\"\n\n    def test_missing_position_id_yields_empty_url(self):\n        jobs = parse_apple(\"apple\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"postingTitle\": \"Eng\"}])\n        assert jobs[0].url == \"\"\n```\n\n**Remaining `parse_*` functions needing the same treatment** (same categories: happy path, missing-optional-key defaults, empty input, malformed nested dict) ã not skeletoned individually to avoid repetition, but each is currently 0% covered:\n\n| Function | Key edge case to cover |\n|---|---|\n| `parse_recruitee` | flat-string location vs assembled city/country |\n| `parse_workable` | dict vs non-dict `location` shape (two branches) |\n| `parse_smartrecruiters` | location string built from 3 optional parts, one/two/all missing |\n| `parse_deshaw` | regex-based HTML parsing: malformed card, missing title/id (skipped), duplicate `data-job-id` (dedup via `seen`) |\n| `parse_twosigma` | triple-rendered card dedup via `seen`, location lookup bounded to next anchor |\n| `parse_optiver` | `href` prefix stripping (`join-us/jobs/` removal), relative vs absolute URL |\n| `parse_eightfold` | `location` string vs `locations` list-with-commas fallback |\n| `parse_phenom` | `jobId` vs `jobSeqNo` fallback, `cityStateCountry` vs assembled fallback |\n| `parse_microsoft` | `standardizedLocations` vs `locations` fallback, `postedTs` present/absent |\n| `parse_netflix` | `locations` list vs singular `location` fallback, `t_create` vs `t_update` fallback |\n| `parse_bytedance` | `job_url.format(id=...)` when `id` missing |\n\n#### 6c. `fetch_*` async functions ã untested pagination/dedup loops (real bug-prone logic)\n\nThe recurring pattern across `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_apple`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_bytedance`, `fetch_phenom`, `fetch_google`: paginate until a page returns *no fresh* IDs, tracking a `seen` set. None of these loops are tested for:\n- Stopping correctly when a page returns only already-seen IDs (not just empty).\n- Respecting `max_pages` as a hard cap even if the server keeps returning fresh data forever (protects against a server bug causing infinite pagination).\n- `fetch_workday`'s different-shaped stop condition (`offset >= total or offset > 5000`).\n- `fetch_ashby`'s 200ã404 branching (posting-api available vs disabled-fallback-to-HTML) and the \"neither works\" `RuntimeError`.\n- `fetch_meta`'s token-scraping regexes and the `\"for (;;);\"` XSSI-prefix strip, plus the `errors` key ã `RuntimeError` path (this is the doc_id-rotation failure mode the module docstring specifically warns about).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nimport httpx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver, fetch_ashby, fetch_meta, fetch_workday\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchOptiverPagination:\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_stops_when_page_has_no_fresh_ids(self):\n        respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(side_effect=[\n            httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/a\", \"title\": \"A\"}]}),\n            httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": []}),\n        ])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 5})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_respects_max_pages_cap(self):\n        route = respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [\n                {\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/x\", \"title\": \"Always fresh\"}]}))\n        # server pretends to always have (the same, so actually not-fresh) data;\n        # verify loop terminates via the not-fresh check well before max_pages\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 100})\n        assert route.call_count <= 2  # first page + one confirming empty\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchAshby:\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_uses_posting_api_when_available(self):\n        respx.get(url__regex=r\".*api\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"Eng\"}]}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_falls_back_to_hosted_page_on_404(self):\n        respx.get(url__regex=r\".*api\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        html = ('<script>window.__appData = {\"jobBoard\":{\"jobPostings\":'\n                '[{\"id\":\"2\",\"title\":\"Eng\"}]}};</script>')\n        respx.get(url__regex=r\".*jobs\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=html))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n        assert jobs[0].external_id == \"2\"\n\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_raises_when_neither_source_available(self):\n        respx.get(url__regex=r\".*api\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        respx.get(url__regex=r\".*jobs\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"<html>no appdata here</html>\"))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"no posting-api\"):\n                await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchMeta:\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_raises_runtime_error_when_graphql_errors_present(self):\n        # simulates the doc_id-rotation failure the module docstring warns about\n        respx.get(\"https://www.metacareers.com/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='[\"LSD\",[],{\"token\":\"tok\"}]'))\n        respx.post(\"https://www.metacareers.com/graphql\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='for (;;);{\"errors\":[{\"message\":\"bad doc_id\"}]}'))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"bad doc_id\"):\n                await fetch_meta(client, {\"company\": \"meta\"})\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchWorkday:\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_stops_at_total_offset(self):\n        respx.post(url__regex=r\".*wday/cxs.*\").mock(side_effect=[\n            httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": \"A\", \"bulletFields\": [\"R1\"]}],\n                                       \"total\": 1}),\n        ])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n```\n\n#### 6d. `fetch_all` / `fetch_source` ã the concurrency/error-isolation contract, untested\n\n- `fetch_source`: unknown `ats` value raises `ValueError` listing known ATS names ã untested.\n- `fetch_all`: one source's fetcher raising must not abort the others (mirrors the `notify.dispatch` isolation gap) ã the module's core resilience promise, unverified. Also: `concurrency` semaphore is never asserted to actually bound in-flight requests, and the \"owns_client\" cleanup (`aclose()` only called when `fetch_all` created its own client) is untested.\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        from fetchers import fetch_source\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"nonexistent\"})\n\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_abort_others(self, monkeypatch):\n        import fetchers\n        async def boom(client, source):\n            raise RuntimeError(\"network down\")\n        async def ok(client, source):\n            return [object()]  # stand-in Job\n        monkeypatch.setitem(fetchers.FETCHERS, \"greenhouse\", boom)\n        monkeypatch.setitem(fetchers.FETCHERS, \"lever\", ok)\n        result = await fetchers.fetch_all([\n            {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"a\"},\n            {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"b\"},\n        ])\n        assert len(result) == 1  # only lever's result survived\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` ã CLI/deterministic-helper layer, zero coverage\n\n**Untested, in order of risk:**\n\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run window (`marker is None` ã `since_days` fallback) vs subsequent-run (marker present); `--posted-days` filtering with `--dated-only` on/off (three-way branch: dated-and-fresh kept, dated-and-old dropped, undated kept-unless-dated-only); group-boundary truncation logic (`groupby` on `first_seen` ã must never split a `first_seen` group even when it exceeds `--limit`, per the code comment) ã this truncation/watermark interaction is genuinely subtle and currently has no test proving the \"never split a group\" guarantee.\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now` path, explicit watermark path, invalid ISO string ã exit code 2 + stderr message, neither arg given ã exit code 2.\n- `cmd_report_num`: delegates to `Store.next_seq`, zero-padding format (`003` not `3`).\n- `_normalize_ats`: the ATS character-replacement table ã must apply inside body text but explicitly must NOT apply inside `<style>`/`<script>` blocks or HTML tag attributes (this exclusion is the entire point of the function's two-pass regex split and is unverified); counts dict accuracy.\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: file-not-found ã exit 2; happy path needs a real Chrome binary (should be marked `@pytest.mark.integration` / skipped in CI without Chrome) ã at minimum, `_normalize_ats` and the `--format`/page-css injection and missing-`</head>` fallback should be unit tested without invoking Chrome at all.\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env override, PATH lookup via `shutil.which`, macOS `.app` bundle fallback, `sys.exit` when none found.\n- `main()`'s argv routing: `db-new`/`db-mark`/`pdf-render`/`report-num`/`-h` dispatch, bare invocation ã interactive, mode words stopping at first flag (`mode_words, extra = words[:i], words[i:]`).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport json\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nimport agent\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef db_with_jobs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.chdir(tmp_path)\n    (tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\").write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as s:\n        s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\",\n                     posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())])\n    return tmp_path\n\nclass TestCmdDbNew:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, db_with_jobs, capsys):\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"--since-days\", \"7\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n    def test_dated_only_drops_undated_jobs(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        monkeypatch.chdir(tmp_path)\n        (tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\").write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as s:\n            s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\",\n                         url=\"u\", posted_at=\"\")])  # no posted_at\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"--dated-only\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"undated_dropped\"] == 1\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 0\n\n    def test_posted_days_keeps_undated_without_dated_only(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        monkeypatch.chdir(tmp_path)\n        (tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\").write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as s:\n            s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\",\n                         url=\"u\", posted_at=\"\")])\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"--posted-days\", \"7\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"undated_kept\"] == 1\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n    def test_truncation_never_splits_a_first_seen_group(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        monkeypatch.chdir(tmp_path)\n        (tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\").write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as s:\n            jobs = [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n                    for i in range(5)]\n            s.diff(jobs)  # all 5 share one first_seen timestamp\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"--limit\", \"3\"])  # limit smaller than the group\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 5  # whole group kept, not truncated to 3\n        assert out[\"truncated\"] is False\n\n\nclass TestCmdDbMark:\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_timestamp(self, db_with_jobs, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\"])\n        assert rc == 0\n        assert \"scan marker ->\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    def test_invalid_watermark_exits_2(self, db_with_jobs, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"])\n        assert rc == 2\n        assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n    def test_no_args_exits_2(self, db_with_jobs, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_smart_quotes_in_body_text(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d</p>\")\n        assert '\"Hello\"' in html\n        assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_block(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\n            \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\")\n        assert html.count(\"\\u2014\") == 1  # only the <style> one survives\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats('<a title=\"em\\u2014dash\">text</a>')\n        assert 'title=\"em\\u2014dash\"' in html  # attribute untouched\n        assert \"em-dash\" not in counts\n\n\nclass TestChromeBin:\n    def test_chrome_path_env_var_used_when_file_exists(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        fake = tmp_path / \"chrome\"\n        fake.write_text(\"\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", str(fake))\n        assert agent._chrome_bin() == str(fake)\n\n    def test_exits_when_nothing_found(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", raising=False)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent.shutil, \"which\", lambda name: None)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent.Path, \"exists\", lambda self: False)\n        with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n            agent._chrome_bin()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py` ã thin argparse wrapper, minimal but currently 0% covered\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport cli\n\ndef test_main_passes_config_and_dry_run_to_run_sync():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"-c\", \"custom.yaml\", \"--dry-run\"]):\n            cli.main()\n        mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"custom.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n\ndef test_main_defaults_config_path():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\"]):\n            cli.main()\n        mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=False)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Priority ranking if coverage is added incrementally\n\n1. **`models.py` + `filters.py`** ã pure functions, no mocking needed, highest ROI, catches dedup/filter-matching bugs (the app's actual correctness contract).\n2. **`store.py`** ã the dedup source of truth; a bug here silently re-notifies or silently drops jobs, and it's the one module with real state/concurrency semantics (`next_seq`'s `BEGIN IMMEDIATE`) worth locking down.\n3. **`fetchers.py` `parse_*` functions** ã cheapest to test (pure, no I/O) and the most frequently-breaking code in this repo per your own memory notes (Meta's doc_id rotation, ByteDance schema strictness, Microsoft's URL migration) ã regression tests here would have caught prior incidents you've already hit.\n4. **`agent.py` `cmd_db_new` truncation/watermark logic** ã subtle enough that a bug would silently corrupt what the scan pipeline sees, worth locking down given [[jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions]] already shows this pipeline has had state-corruption issues.\n5. **`notify.py` + `fetch_*` async functions** ã need `respx`/env mocking, more setup cost, but protect against silent notification loss and pagination