        "content": "\nEvery parser has the same untested edge-case shape: missing optional keys, empty result arrays, `isListed: False` / dedup filtering (Ashby), malformed nested location dicts, and required-key `KeyError` behavior when a source omits `id`/`title` (several parsers do `j[\"id\"]` unguarded ã e.g. `parse_greenhouse`, `parse_lever`, `parse_smartrecruiters` ã a source returning a job without an `id` currently crashes the whole fetch instead of skipping that one row, and nothing documents or tests this).\n\nFull skeleton for `parse_greenhouse` (representative) plus the trickier bespoke ones (`_amazon_posted_at`, `_apple_hydration`, `_ds1_posted_at`, `_bd_location`) that have real parsing-logic bugs waiting to happen:\n\n```python\n",
