        "title": "6d. `fetch_all` / `fetch_source` ã the concurrency/error-isolation contract, untested",
        "content": "\n- `fetch_source`: unknown `ats` value raises `ValueError` listing known ATS names ã untested.\n- `fetch_all`: one source's fetcher raising must not abort the others (mirrors the `notify.dispatch` isolation gap) ã the module's core resilience promise, unverified. Also: `concurrency` semaphore is never asserted to actually bound in-flight requests, and the \"owns_client\" cleanup (`aclose()` only called when `fetch_all` created its own client) is untested.\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        from fetchers import fetch_source\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"nonexistent\"})\n\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_abort_others(self, monkeypatch):\n        import fetchers\n        async def boom(client, source):\n            raise RuntimeError(\"network down\")\n        async def ok(client, source):\n            return [object()]  # stand-in Job\n        monkeypatch.setitem(fetchers.FETCHERS, \"greenhouse\", boom)\n        monkeypatch.setitem(fetchers.FETCHERS, \"lever\", ok)\n        result = await fetchers.fetch_all([\n            {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"a\"},\n            {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"b\"},\n        ])\n        assert len(result) == 1  # only lever's result survived\n```\n\n---\n\n",
